AGI -&nbsp; Ukraine has proven to be ready for a truce, now it is up to Russia to respond. "Today it depends 100% on Moscow - said Zelensky - America showed its position, Ukraine showed its position, and today Russia must respond>", he said in a press conference in Kiev.&nbsp;
"We will talk about security guarantees in more detail if there will be a ceasefire for 30 days. These 30 days are designed to put black on white the passages we agreed with allies and the format of security guarantees that will be in place in Ukraine after the end of the war", said Zelensky.&nbsp;
In addition, the Ukrainian president reiterated that he was ready to call elections only "after the end of the war".
"After the end of the war, martial law will be revoked and after the revocation of martial law > the elections will be held in accordance with Ukrainian law. No one will refer anything on purpose," Zelensky explained during a press briefing in Kiev, as reported by the Unian agency.
Zelensky's mandate expired last year but it is not legally possible to hold elections while martial law is in force.
<h2> Russia regains Sudzha in Kursk</h2>
The Russian flag was raised in the administration of Sudzha, a town in the Kursk Oblast, near the Ukrainian border. "The center of the city has returned to the control of the Russian federation," announced in Ria Novosti the commander of battalion of the northern group of Russian forces.
Moscow also claimed the reconquest of five villages in the region. "The units of the group of forces of the north - it has announced the defense - they have continued their offensive and have resumed control of Kazachya Loknya, Pervyi Kzhnyay, Vtoroi Knyazhy, Zamostye and Mirny", said the ministry of Moscow. The Russian army, according to Moscow, has rejected a Ukrainian counterattack in the region in the last 24 hours.
&nbsp;
